{"block1":"<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Hemorrhoids are bundles of nerves that swell and become sensitive. Depending on the location of your hemorrhoids, you may experience different symptoms, and in varying severity. While <a href=\"http:\/\/hemorrhoidreport.net\/hemorrhoid-information\/medications-for-internal-hemorrhoids\/\"  >internal hemorrhoids<\/a> are less painful, they may cause you to pass bright red blood, which can be alarming at first. External hemorrhoids are more irritating, causing intense itching and pain. The following article offers some helpful information about hemorrhoids.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"\/images\/portrait-of-fiber-supplements.jpg\" class=\"img_right \" alt=\"portrait of fiber supplements\" style=\"float: right; padding: 8px; padding-right: 0;\" \/><\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you don&#39;t consume many vegetable and fruits, take a fiber supplement daily. Take the supplements&nbsp;throughout the day, and don&#39;t forget to drink your eight glasses of water.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Tomatoes can help reduce hemorrhoids. The acidic composition of the tomato can provide relief for the swelling when it is applied to the swollen area. When paired with a nutritious diet, this treatment can prevent hemorrhoids. An enema can take away the pain.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Dice about two cloves of garlic and steep them for at least 30 minutes in boiling hot water. Allow the water to cool down. Then, when it&#39;s at room temperature, use the water to give yourself an enema once each day.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"\/images\/portrait-of-a-woman-in-the-bath-tub.jpg\" class=\"img_left \" alt=\"portrait of a woman in the bath tub\" style=\"float: left; padding: 8px; padding-left: 0;\" \/><\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">When <a href=\"annoying-hemorrhoids-try-these-tips-for-some-quick-relief\"  >dealing with hemorrhoids<\/a>, be careful not to expose the affected areas to products containing dyes, essential oils, or fragrances. Allowing the hemorrhoid to come in contact with substances like these for even a brief moment can bring on pain, stinging, and exacerbated swelling.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Drinking a moderate amount of caffeine is good for both keeping you alert and helping to control hemorrhoids. Constipation and hard stool are two major factors in the formation of hemorrhoids, and caffeine stimulation can make movements easier.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Thoroughly cleaning your rectal area is essential if you have hemorrhoids. Moistened wipes are much better than using toilet paper because they are&nbsp;more comfortable. A warm sitz bath&nbsp;can soothe swelling and pain from hemorrhoids. Try to soak for around 20 minutes.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The more you understand about hemorrhoids, the better your chances of dealing with them&nbsp;effectively.&nbsp;Acquire as much knowledge as you can so that you can help yourself, or a loved one who is&nbsp;suffering . The symptoms of hemorrhoids were covered at the beginning of this article. External and internal hemorrhoids can produce different symptoms and levels of pain,&nbsp;and are&nbsp;easy to distinguish because of this. By following the advice in this article, you can learn more about the prevention and treatment of hemorrhoids.<\/p>\r\n"}